Getting Started

    Clone the Repository: ```bash git clone https://github.com/<username>/vibe-patches.git cd vibe-patches ```

    Install Dependencies: Vibe Patches uses standard libraries (e.g., tkinter, ast) included with Python 3.6+.

    Run the Application: ```bash python vibe_patch.py ``` To open a file directly: ```bash python vibe_patch.py path/to/your_file.py ```

    Using the Tool:

        Click the Open button to load a Python file.

        Select a patchable item from the dropdown list.

        Edit the patch text in the patch area.

        Click Apply Patch to update the file, or use Revert to roll back to the latest backup.

